WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:20.000
[Outdoor residential fire simulation. Two house-scale wooden structures. Firefighter ignites fire inside both using a blowtorch.]

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:45.000
[Video plays at 4x speed. Both structures begin to show fire activity.]

00:00:45.000 --> 00:01:15.000
[UNTREATED structure: flames spread rapidly through the entire frame.]

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:30.000
[Graphic on screen: "Eco-Friendly — AF31 is water-based and environmentally safe."]

00:01:30.000 --> 00:02:00.000
[UNTREATED structure: fully engulfed in flames at accelerated speed.]

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:15.000
[Graphic on screen: "Water Based — non-toxic formula safe for people, animals, and the environment."]

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:50.000
[UNTREATED structure collapses. Text on screen: "Complete Fire Loss."]

00:02:50.000 --> 00:03:05.000
[Graphic on screen: "Unlimited Utility — effective across wood frame, wildfire, and battery applications."]

00:03:05.000 --> 00:04:00.000
[AF31-TREATED structure: fire burns only initial ignition material. Flames do not spread to treated wood.]

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:45.000
[AF31-TREATED structure: fire self-extinguishes. Structure remains fully intact.]

00:04:45.000 --> 00:05:05.000
[Final comparison displayed. M-Fire Suppression branding and contact information shown.]
